curity-testing/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 4}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136848", "title": "The Download: inside the Musk v. Altman trial, and AI for democracy", "summary": "This is today&#8217;s edition of The Download, our weekday newsletter that provides a daily dose of what&#8217;s going on in the world of technology. Week one of the Musk v. Altman trial: what it was like in the room Two of the most powerful figures in AI\u2014Sam Altman and Elon Musk\u2014are in the middle o...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/05/05/1136848/the-download-musk-openai-altman-trial-ai-democracy/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 3}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136843", "title": "A blueprint for using AI to strengthen democracy", "summary": "Every few centuries, changes in how information moves reshape how societies govern themselves. The printing press spread vernacular literacy, helping give rise to the Reformation and, eventually, representative government. The telegraph made it possible to administer vast nations like the US, accele...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/05/05/1136843/ai-democracy-blueprint/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=35148", "title": "Meta now scans photos for bone structure and body size to flag minors on Instagram and Facebook", "summary": "Meta uses AI-supported image analysis to recognize minors on Instagram and Facebook, based on visual characteristics such as body size or bone structure, not facial recognition, as the company emphasizes.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/meta-now-scans-photos-for-bone-structure-and-body-size-to-flag-minors-on-instagram-and-facebook/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 2}], "today_tech": [{"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2605.02908v1", "title": "Memorization In Stable Diffusion Is Unexpectedly Driven by CLIP Embeddings", "summary": "Abstract: U